# Implement Cursor Tool Call Normalization

Extend the output normalization pipeline to handle tool call lifecycle (started/completed) and map all 11 tool types to ActionType format.

## Scope

**Extend `src/agents/cursor/normalizer/` directory:**

### 1. Tool Mapping Functions (`mappers.ts`)
```typescript
export function mapToolToAction(
  toolCall: CursorToolCall,
  workDir: string
): { actionType: ActionType; content: string } {
  // Map each of 11 tools to ActionType
  // - shell → command_run
  // - read → file_read
  // - write → file_write (initially, before result)
  // - edit → file_edit with changes
  // - delete → file_edit with delete change
  // - grep/semsearch → search
  // - todo → todo_management
  // - mcp → tool
  // - glob/ls → other
  // - unknown → other
}

export function mapToolToActionWithResult(
  toolCall: CursorToolCall,
  workDir: string
): { actionType: ActionType; content: string } {
  // Same as above but include results
  // - shell: extract exitCode, stdout, stderr
  // - edit: extract unified diff from result
  // - mcp: extract markdown from content array
}
```

### 2. Tool Call Lifecycle Handling (in `state.ts`)
```typescript
handleToolCallStarted(
  message: CursorToolCallMessage,
  workDir: string
): NormalizedEntry | null {
  const toolName = getToolName(message.tool_call);
  const { actionType, content } = mapToolToAction(message.tool_call, workDir);

  const index = this.nextIndex();
  const entry: NormalizedEntry = {
    index,
    type: {
      kind: 'tool_use',
      tool: {
        toolName,
        action: actionType,
        status: 'created',
      },
    },
    content,
    timestamp: new Date(),
  };

  // Track call_id → index for result merging
  this.toolCalls.set(message.call_id!, { index, entry });
  return entry;
}

handleToolCallCompleted(
  message: CursorToolCallMessage,
  workDir: string
): NormalizedEntry | null {
  const existing = this.toolCalls.get(message.call_id!);
  if (!existing) return null;

  // Update with result
  const { actionType, content } = mapToolToActionWithResult(
    message.tool_call,
    workDir
  );

  return {
    index: existing.index,  // SAME index as started
    type: {
      kind: 'tool_use',
      tool: {
        toolName: getToolName(message.tool_call),
        action: actionType,
        status: 'success',  // or 'failed' based on result
      },
    },
    content,
    timestamp: new Date(),
  };
}
```

### 3. Shell Tool Result Parsing
```typescript
function parseShellResult(toolCall: CursorShellTool): CommandResult | undefined {
  const result = toolCall.result?.success || toolCall.result?.failure;
  if (!result) return undefined;

  return {
    exitCode: result.exitCode ?? 0,
    stdout: result.stdout ?? '',
    stderr: result.stderr ?? '',
  };
}
```

### 4. MCP Tool Result Extraction
```typescript
function parseMcpResult(toolCall: CursorMcpTool): string {
  const content = toolCall.result?.success?.content 
    || toolCall.result?.failure?.content 
    || [];

  return content
    .map(item => item.text?.text || '')
    .filter(Boolean)
    .join('\n\n');
}
```

### 5. Path Utilities
```typescript
function makePathRelative(absolutePath: string, workDir: string): string {
  if (absolutePath.startsWith(workDir)) {
    return absolutePath.slice(workDir.length).replace(/^\//, '');
  }
  return absolutePath;
}
```

## Tool-Specific Handling

### Shell Tool
- Started: `ActionType.command_run` with command, no result
- Completed: Add `CommandResult` with exitCode, stdout, stderr

### Edit Tool (3 strategies)
- **applyPatch**: Extract hunks from `patchContent`
- **strReplace**: Create diff from old_text → new_text
- **multiStrReplace**: Concatenate multiple diffs
- Fallback: Use `diffString` from result if available

### MCP Tool
- Extract provider identifier
- Extract tool name
- Parse content array to markdown
- Map to `ActionType.tool`

### Read/Write/Delete Tools
- Map to appropriate `ActionType`
- Make paths relative to workDir

### Grep/SemSearch Tools
- Map to `ActionType.search` with query

### Todo Tool
- Map to `ActionType.todo_management`
- Extract todos array and operation

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All 11 tool types mapped to ActionType
- [ ] Unknown tools handled with fallback
- [ ] Tool call lifecycle (started → completed) working
- [ ] Shell results parsed correctly (exitCode, stdout, stderr)
- [ ] Edit tool handles all 3 strategies
- [ ] MCP results extracted to markdown
- [ ] Paths made relative to workDir
- [ ] Complete JSDoc documentation
- [ ] Unit tests for all 11 tools + unknown
- [ ] Unit tests for lifecycle (started → completed)
- [ ] Unit tests for edit strategies

